metadata.creator: fuellsand
metadata.description: Part two of the ep trilogy. "dyskoteka", polish for discotheque, opens with a sample you should recognize by yourself in its unique sound asthetics. Within the song an organ appears for the first time, even tough there are bouncing synths and distorted guitars. "troutfishing" develops with a recognizable B4-motive and the straight use of live drums a more rockish atmosphere than the previous released tracks.
metadata.title: Fuellsand - Two Songs For The Summer [12rec.007]
